ome to be understood as typical of life on all such ships.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAntislavery movementsxHistoryxGreat BritainxGro→britannien. 0aAntislavery movementszGreat BritainxHistory. 0aMarine insurancexHistoryxGreat Britain. 0aMarine insurancezGreat BritainxHistory. 0aMass murderxHistoryx18th century. 0aMass murderxHistoryy18th century. 0aSeafaring lifexHistoryx18th century. 0aSeafaring lifexHistoryy18th century. 0aSlave tradexHistoryx18th centuryxEnglandxLiverpool. 0aSlave tradexHistoryx18th centuryxJamaica. 0aSlave tradezEnglandzLiverpoolxHistoryy18th century. 0aSlave tradezJamaicaxHistoryy18th century. 0aSlaveryxLaw and legislationxHistoryxGreat Britain. 0aSlaveryxLaw and legislationzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aSlavesxViolence againstxHistoryx18th century. 0aSlavesxViolence againstxHistoryy18th century. 0aTrialsxHistoryx18th centuryxEnglandxLondon. 0aTrialszEnglandzLondonxHistoryy18th century. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 18th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018075640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300180756423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300180756/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles